<div class="page-home">
	<h1>How do you eat an elephant? One bite at a time.</h1>
	<div class="buttons">
		<% if user_signed_in? %>
			<%= link_to "View my TaskFractal", tasks_path, class: 'button-link primary' %>
		<% else %>
			<%= link_to "Sign in", new_user_session_path, class: 'button-link primary' %>
			<%= link_to "Sign up", new_user_registration_path, class: 'button-link secondary' %>
		<% end %>
	</div>
	<div class="row">
		<p>The best way to handle a tough project is to break it into manageable chunks. <strong>TaskFractal</strong> lets you break projects into chunks, and then break the chunks into smaller pieces, and so on as deep as you want.</p>
		<img src="/home/outline.png" alt="Outline view">
	</div>
	<div class="work-on-next">
		<h1>Always know what to work on next</h1>
		<picture>
			<source srcset="/home/next-up.png" media="(min-width: 1000px)">
			<img src="/home/next-up-mobile.png" alt="NextUp offers two tasks, ready to be worked on" class="img-center">
		</picture>
		<p class="align-center">Cut through the clutter. TaskFractal will always give you two things you can work on right now.</p>
	</div>
	<h1>Everything in one place</h1>
	<div class="features-grid">
		<i data-feather='paperclip'></i>
		<p>Attach everything you need to complete the task so you donâ€™t have to go hunting for it when the time is right.</p>
		<i data-feather='camera'></i>
		<p>Snap photos with your phone and attach them to the task for reference.</p>
		<i data-feather='align-left'></i>
		<p>Take notes on each task. Write down addresses, details, and how-to's.</p>
	</div>
	<footer>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="https://github.com/DawnPaladin/TaskFractal">Source code</a></li>
			<li>By <a href="https://jamesharris.design">James Harris</a></li>
			<li><a href="mailto:computersherpa@gmail.com">Contact me</a></li>
		</ul>
	</footer>
</div>

<style>
html, body {
	margin: 0;
	height: 100%;
	background: #0F296A;
}

<% unless user_signed_in? %>
header {
	display: none;
}
<% end %>
</style>
